@startuml 34_async_d1_d2_d3_flows
!theme plain
title DRE 3D Framework -- Async Flows (D1 Detection → D2 Diagnosis → D3 Deflection)

skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #546E7A
  LifeLineBorderColor #B0BEC5
  ParticipantBorderColor #90A4AE
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #ECEFF1
  BoxBorderColor #CFD8DC
}

box "Triggers" #FFF3E0
  participant "Cron Schedule\nUpstream Job" as Trigger
  participant "Pipeline\nFailure Event" as PipelineEvent
end box

box "D1 Detection (Workflow)" #FFCDD2
  participant "Pipeline Failure\nMonitor" as PFM
  participant "Anomaly Detection\nJob" as D1Job
  participant "Profiler &\nBaseline Learner" as Profiler
end box

box "Unity Catalog Delta" #E3F2FD
  database "anomaly_check_config\n+ pipeline_registry" as ConfigDB
  database "incident_context\n(Unified Signal)" as IncidentDB
  database "DIGITAL_DATA_ANOMALIES" as AnomDB
  database "table_daily_metrics\n(Baselines)" as MetricsDB
  database "diagnosis_evidence_log" as EvidenceDB
  database "deployment_registry" as DeployDB
  database "incident_kb\n(Learning)" as IncidentKB
end box

box "D2 Diagnosis (Workflow)" #F8BBD0
  participant "Signal\nClassifier" as SignalClass
  participant "Evidence\nRetriever" as EvidenceAgent
  participant "Deployment\nCorrelator" as DeployCorr
  participant "Playbook\nCompiler" as PlaybookAgent
end box

box "D3 Deflection (Workflow)" #CE93D8
  participant "State\nValidator" as StateValidator
  participant "Circuit\nBreaker" as CircuitBreaker
  participant "Approval\nGate" as ApprovalGate
  participant "Domain\nExecutor" as DomainExec
  participant "Feedback\nLearner" as FeedbackAgent
end box

box "External Systems" #FFF9C4
  participant "Databricks\nJob Logs" as JobLogs
  participant "Delta History\n+ UC Metadata" as DeltaMeta
  participant "Jira + GitHub\nConfluence + ITSM" as External
end box

box "AI & RAG" #FFF8E1
  participant "Mosaic AI\nLLM" as LLM
  participant "AI Search\nVector Index" as VS
end box

==ASYNC FLOW 1: Scheduled D1 Detection==

Trigger -> D1Job : Cron trigger (daily 02:00 UTC)
activate D1Job

D1Job -> ConfigDB : SELECT rules\nWHERE is_active = true\nAND frequency = 'daily'

ConfigDB --> D1Job : Active rules (247)

D1Job -> MetricsDB : Load baselines\n(EWMA, stddev, PSI)

MetricsDB --> D1Job : Baseline data

D1Job -> D1Job : Execute DQ checks:\n- Z-score (volume anomaly)\n- Null rate\n- Freshness SLA\n- Distribution drift

alt Anomaly Detected
  D1Job -> AnomDB : INSERT anomaly\n(table: gold.customer,\nseverity: HIGH, z_score: 3.2)
  
  D1Job -> IncidentDB : INSERT incident_context\n(signal_source: DATA_ANOMALY,\nfailure_class: STATISTICAL)
  
  D1Job -> External : Send P1 alert\n(Jira + Email)
  
  D1Job -> D1Job : Trigger D2 workflow
else No Anomaly
  D1Job -> ConfigDB : Log execution (PASS)
end

deactivate D1Job

note right
  <b>D1 Flow Complete</b>
  Scheduled execution
  Writes to Delta
  Triggers D2 on anomaly
end note

==ASYNC FLOW 2: Pipeline Failure Detection==

PipelineEvent -> PFM : Pipeline failure event\n(job_id: 12345, run_id: 67890)
activate PFM

PFM -> JobLogs : Query run logs\n(stderr, exit code)

JobLogs --> PFM : Task failed: TIMEOUT\nError: "Connection refused"

PFM -> ConfigDB : Query pipeline_registry\n(owner, criticality, deps)

ConfigDB --> PFM : {owner: "team-data",\ncriticality: "HIGH",\nupstream_deps: [pipeline_A, pipeline_B]}

PFM -> IncidentDB : INSERT incident_context\n(signal_source: PIPELINE_FAILURE,\nerror_type: TASK_TIMEOUT,\nfailure_class: INFRA)

PFM -> AnomDB : INSERT anomaly\n(severity: CRITICAL)

PFM -> External : Send P1 alert

PFM -> PFM : Trigger D2 workflow

deactivate PFM

note right
  <b>Pipeline Failure Flow Complete</b>
  Event-driven detection
  Unified incident_context
  Triggers D2 immediately
end note

==ASYNC FLOW 3: D2 Diagnosis==

IncidentDB -> SignalClass : New incident\n(diagnosis_status: PENDING)
activate SignalClass

SignalClass -> IncidentDB : Read incident_context

IncidentDB --> SignalClass : {signal_source: PIPELINE_FAILURE,\nerror_type: TASK_TIMEOUT}

SignalClass -> SignalClass : Classify:\nPipeline vs Data?\nInfra vs Code vs Data?

SignalClass --> SignalClass : Classification:\nPIPELINE_FAILURE / INFRA

SignalClass -> EvidenceAgent : Gather evidence\n(incident_context)
deactivate SignalClass

activate EvidenceAgent

EvidenceAgent -> JobLogs : Retrieve job logs\n(Jobs API 2.1)
JobLogs --> EvidenceAgent : Task stderr/stdout

EvidenceAgent -> DeltaMeta : DESCRIBE HISTORY\n(affected table)
DeltaMeta --> EvidenceAgent : Recent operations (MERGE, DELETE)

EvidenceAgent -> External : Confluence: Search runbooks\n(keyword: "timeout")
External --> EvidenceAgent : Runbook: "Timeout Troubleshooting"

EvidenceAgent -> External : GitHub: Code search\n(pipeline code)
External --> EvidenceAgent : Recent commit: 2h ago

EvidenceAgent -> External : ITSM: Prior incidents\n(same error_type)
External --> EvidenceAgent : 2 similar incidents (resolved)

EvidenceAgent -> VS : RAG: Search incident_kb\n(embed: "task timeout infra")
VS --> EvidenceAgent : Similar incidents (3)

EvidenceAgent -> DeployCorr : Correlate deployment
deactivate EvidenceAgent

activate DeployCorr

DeployCorr -> DeployDB : Query recent deployments\n(last 4 hours)

DeployDB --> DeployCorr : Deployment: 13:45 UTC\n(bundle: v2.3.1 → v2.3.2)

DeployCorr -> External : GitHub: Compare commits
External --> DeployCorr : Config change: timeout 60s → 30s

DeployCorr -> PlaybookAgent : Evidence + correlation
deactivate DeployCorr

activate PlaybookAgent

PlaybookAgent -> LLM : Compile evidence into playbook\n(job_log + delta_history + runbook\n+ code + deployment)

LLM --> PlaybookAgent : Root cause:\n"Timeout reduced in v2.3.2\nTask needs 45s but timeout is 30s"\n\nPrescription:\n"Rollback to v2.3.1 OR\nIncrease timeout to 60s"

PlaybookAgent -> EvidenceDB : INSERT evidence_bundle\n(complete diagnostic context)

PlaybookAgent -> IncidentDB : UPDATE incident_context\n(diagnosis_status: READY_FOR_DEFLECTION)

PlaybookAgent -> PlaybookAgent : Trigger D3 workflow

deactivate PlaybookAgent

note right
  <b>D2 Flow Complete</b>
  Multi-source evidence
  Deployment correlation
  LLM compiles playbook
  Triggers D3
end note

==ASYNC FLOW 4: D3 Deflection==

IncidentDB -> StateValidator : diagnosis_status:\nREADY_FOR_DEFLECTION
activate StateValidator

StateValidator -> JobLogs : Re-check: Is failure still present?

JobLogs --> StateValidator : Yes, job still failing

StateValidator -> CircuitBreaker : Validate remediation eligibility
deactivate StateValidator

activate CircuitBreaker

CircuitBreaker -> EvidenceDB : Load evidence_bundle

EvidenceDB --> CircuitBreaker : Full diagnostic context

CircuitBreaker -> ConfigDB : Query remediation_policy\n(pipeline_id)

ConfigDB --> CircuitBreaker : {auto_fix_allowed: true,\nmax_retries: 3,\nblast_radius_threshold: 10,\napproval_required: true\n(config change)}

CircuitBreaker -> CircuitBreaker : Check:\n- blast_radius: 1 pipeline (OK)\n- PII table: No (OK)\n- Config change: Yes (APPROVAL REQUIRED)

CircuitBreaker -> ApprovalGate : Route to approval
deactivate CircuitBreaker

activate ApprovalGate

ApprovalGate -> LLM : Format diagnostic summary\n(human-readable)

LLM --> ApprovalGate : "Pipeline 'customer_load' failing\ndue to timeout config change.\n\nRoot Cause: v2.3.2 reduced timeout\nfrom 60s to 30s. Task needs 45s.\n\nProposed Fix: Rollback to v2.3.1\nOR increase timeout to 60s.\n\nRisk: Low (config-only change)\nBlast Radius: 1 pipeline"

ApprovalGate -> External : Jira: Create approval ticket\n+ Email to PO/TL

External --> ApprovalGate : Approval granted\n(click-to-approve)

ApprovalGate -> DomainExec : Execute approved fix
deactivate ApprovalGate

activate DomainExec

DomainExec -> External : GitHub: Create PR\n(revert timeout config)

DomainExec -> External : Databricks: Deploy fix\n(bundle: v2.3.2 → v2.3.3)

DomainExec -> JobLogs : Restart pipeline\n(with fix)

DomainExec -> DomainExec : Wait for verification run

JobLogs --> DomainExec : Run successful (exit: 0)

DomainExec -> FeedbackAgent : Fix outcome: SUCCESS
deactivate DomainExec

activate FeedbackAgent

FeedbackAgent -> AnomDB : UPDATE status = RESOLVED

FeedbackAgent -> IncidentKB : INSERT resolved incident\n(root_cause + resolution + outcome)

FeedbackAgent -> MetricsDB : Update baseline\n(feedback loop)

FeedbackAgent -> ConfigDB : Update remediation_policy\n(calibration: timeout fixes\nauto-approve in future)

FeedbackAgent -> External : Notification:\n"Incident resolved"

deactivate FeedbackAgent

note right
  <b>D3 Flow Complete</b>
  Policy-gated approval
  Automated fix execution
  E2E verification
  Feedback to learning
end note

legend right
  <b>Async Flows Summary</b>
  
  <b>Flow 1: Scheduled D1 Detection</b>
    Cron → D1 Job
    → Read rules from Delta
    → Execute checks
    → Write anomalies
    → Trigger D2 (if anomaly)
  
  <b>Flow 2: Pipeline Failure Detection</b>
    Event → Pipeline Failure Monitor
    → Query logs + metadata
    → Write incident_context
    → Trigger D2 immediately
  
  <b>Flow 3: D2 Diagnosis</b>
    incident_context (PENDING)
    → Signal Classifier
    → Evidence Retriever (multi-source)
    → Deployment Correlator
    → Playbook Compiler (LLM)
    → Write evidence_log
    → Trigger D3
  
  <b>Flow 4: D3 Deflection</b>
    evidence_bundle (READY_FOR_DEFLECTION)
    → State Validator
    → Circuit Breaker (policy check)
    → Approval Gate (human-in-loop)
    → Domain Executor (fix + verify)
    → Feedback Learner (update KB + policy)
  
  <b>Key Characteristics:</b>
  - <b>Asynchronous:</b> Event-driven workflows
  - <b>Stateless:</b> State stored in Delta
  - <b>Durable:</b> Restart-safe
  - <b>A2A via Delta:</b> Workflows read/write tables
  - <b>Triggered:</b> Status changes trigger next workflow
  - <b>Feedback Loop:</b> D3 updates D1 baselines
  
  <b>Technologies:</b>
  - Databricks Workflows (Execution)
  - Unity Catalog (State storage)
  - Mosaic AI (Reasoning)
  - AI Search (RAG)
  - External APIs (Evidence + Actions)
  
  <b>A2A Communication:</b>
  D1 → Delta → D2 → Delta → D3 → Delta → D1
  (via incident_context, evidence_log, feedback)
endlegend

@enduml
